  4.0.2 + [#13689](https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/13689) works as far as I tested, but 4.0.3 + [#13689](https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/13689) fails to run `RUN` from a Dockerfile:
  
  ```
  $ cat > Dockerfile
  FROM busybox
  RUN echo hello
  $ podman build . -ttest
  STEP 1/2: FROM busybox
  STEP 2/2: RUN echo hello
  error running container: setting file label on "/proc/self/fd/12": lsetxattr /proc/self/fd/12: operation not supported
  ERRO[0005] did not get container create message from subprocess: read |0: i/o timeout
  Error: error building at STEP "RUN echo hello": error while running runtime: exit status 1
  ```
  
  My guess is that [containers/buildah#3630](https://github.com/containers/buildah/pull/3630) started using `label.Relabel` on `/proc/self/fd/123`, internally `label.Relabel` calls `selinux.Chcon` which at the same merge started using `setxattr` instead of `lsetxattr`, however [opencontainers/selinux#173](https://github.com/opencontainers/selinux/pull/173) changed `selinux.Chcon` back to `lsetxattr` which breaks the first PR.
  
  EDIT: Indeed I removed the call to `runLabelStdioPipes` from [containers/buildah#3630](https://github.com/containers/buildah/pull/3630) and `podman build` works again.
  
